<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Environment Minister Meet in Brunei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 4 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN environment ministers met
at an informal setting Tuesday in Brunei Darussalam and discussed
a wide range of issues regarding ASEAN environment cooperation,
said a joint press statement reaching here this evening.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the ministers exchanged views on haze
related matters, adopted the ASEAN Strategic Plan of Action on
Environment (SPAE), attended the launch of the ASEAN Environment
Year (AEY) 2000, reviewed the progress of the preparation of the
ASEAN State of the Environment Report (SoER) 2000 and discussed
upcoming environmental events at the regional and global levels.
</P>
<P>
The statement said AEY 2000 stressed the importance of raising
public awareness on environmental matters and called for efforts
to educate and inculcate the public with the right concept of
environment protection, proper resources utilization as well as on
minimizing waste while the SPAE consists of the key activities to
be implemented over the next five years.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of trans-boundary haze, the statement said, the
ministers held that the haze in Sumatra and Kalimantan in March
was caused mainly by land clearing by some plantation companies
and the ministers expressed strong objection to such irresponsible
behavior.
</P>
<P>
The ministers agreed to take all possible measures to deal with
the culprits and to enforce the zero-burning policy, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the ministers also discussed cooperation in the
protection of coastal and marine environment as well as nature
conservation and biodivesity, agreeing to focus efforts on
sustainable utilization of biological resources and conservation
of ecosystems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
