<HEADLINE> Philippine Telecom Giant Inks GSM Deal With Nokia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Globe Telecom and Nokia
have signed an agreement valued at 170 million U.S. dollars for
the expansion of Globe's Global System for Mobile communications (
GSM),Philippine News Agency said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is the seventh major agreement that Globe has
entered into with Nokia, one of the world's leading mobile phone
suppliers, bringing the total investments between the two
companies since 1994 to approximately 300 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Nokia will expand Globe's GSM 900 and 1800 services in Metro
Manila and Luzon with work scheduled to be completed by the end of
the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
