<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shares Continue to Slide On Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GES topped the volume list as it registered a turnover of 23.33
million units. It was followed by NOL which had 13.25 million
shares done. SingTel was the next with 12.11 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
CityDev led ascent of the day gaining 50 cents to close at 8.25
Singapore dollars. DBS picked up 30 cents to finish at 21.90
Singapore dollars. Shangri edged up 27 cents to end at 2.58
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 was the biggest loser of the day plunging by 480
cents to close at 47.70 Singapore dollars, down more than 26
percent from its peak last month. PacCent sank 140 cents to finish
at 18.70 Singapore dollars. Chartered gave up 90 cents to end at
14.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said that investors took the reported ruling against
Microsoft as the excuse to sell technology stocks.
</P>
<P>
Stung by the tumble in tech shares, players sought refuge in
property and banking stocks, they added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
