<HEADLINE> Tunisia, India Sign Cooperation Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Tunisia and India on Wednesday signed
a number of accords on legal, scientific, cultural and agricultural
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The documents were signed by Tunisian Secretary of State for
Foreign Affairs Taher Sayod and his Indian counterpart Komar Bangar
at the end of the 8th session of the two countries' mixed committee
here.
</P>
<P>
The documents deal with cooperation in legal affairs and
criminal extradition, scientific and technological industries,
agriculture and culture, according to the Tunisia-Africa News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
The sides also signed an agreement on strengthening the
relations between Tunisian Union of Industry, Trade and Handicraft
and the Indian Industrial Confederation.
</P>
<P>
The Tunisian-Indian mixed committee opened its 8th session on
Tuesday to explore new areas of cooperation, enhance close
relations and encourage businessmen from both sides to launch joint
ventures in both countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
