<HEADLINE> Five Killed in Two Road Accidents in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A school bus driver who drove into the back of a plumbing truck
stopped on an interstate in Wichita of Kansas State was killed
Wednesday morning when an aluminum pipe crashed through her
windshield and hit her in the head.
</P>
<P>
Nine children were on the bus which was taking them to
Toussaint L'Ouverture Elementary School. Four of them, aged 6 to
10, suffered bumps and bruises.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday night, four teen-agers were killed when their car
ran off a road and crashed into a driveway embankment in Oneida
County in Wisconsin State.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted local police as saying that the victims were
high school students, and the cause of the accident was being
investigated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
