<HEADLINE> Life Imprisonment for Accessaries in Iranian General Assassination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Intelligence Ministry said
Wednesday two Iranians were sentenced to life imprisonment for
helping military opposition group to assassinate former Vice Chief
of the Joint Staff of Iranian armed forces Ali Sayyad Shirazi.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said that Nassir Hussein Sharifat and Abdulzahra
Tamimi had been arrested by the ministry's forces and confessed to
their role in helping the Mujaheddin Khalq Organization (MKO) to
cross into Iran to assassinate Shirazi.
</P>
<P>
The two men had been working with the Iraqi intelligence agency
in cross border sabotage against Iran and had crossed the border
into and from Iran several times, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
They helped two assassins sneak into Iran who assassinated
Shirazi on April 10, 1999, the ministry said, giving no date of
their arrest and trial.
</P>
<P>
Shirazi was gunned down in front of his house in northern Tehran
by the assassins disguised as city street cleaners. The MKO soon
claimed responsibility for the killing.
</P>
<P>
The Iraq-based MKO said that Shirazi was targeted because he was
responsible for purging and executing military personnel, and
responsible for the death of hundreds of thousands of teenagers in
the war with Iraq (1980-88).
</P>
<P>
Shirazi, born in 1944, served as commander of the Iranian army's
ground forces during the Iran-Iraq war.
</P>
<P>
The MKO was a main political group which had fought against the
former Iranian shah regime, but it was outlawed in 1981 due to
sharp difference with the then Iranian government.
</P>
<P>
During the past decades, the MKO launched various attacks on
Iranian interests inside and outside Iran. In retaliation, the
Iranian armed forces also bombed the MKO bases in Iraq several
times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
