<HEADLINE> Turkey to Hold Naval Exercise in East Mediterranean  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish Naval Force will hold
military exercises, code-named "East Mediterranean-2000," between
April 12 and 22 in the waters of the Aegean and Mediterranean seas.
</P>
<P>
The manoeuvres aim to improve mutual training and cooperation
between the Turkish and its allied naval forces, according to a
written statement issued by the Turkish General Staff Chief
Secretariat on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The scheduled exercises will be carried out under the command of
War Fleet Commander Admiral Metin Atac, starting with the taking-
off of vessels from Turkey's southern Izmir port on April 12.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Naval Force will field frigates, speedboats, and
logistic support vessels as well as helicopters and jets attached
to the Turkish Air Force.
</P>
<P>
The North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), of which Turkey
has been a member since 1952, will send its Permanent Force in the
Mediterranean to participate the manoeuvres.
</P>
<P>
The United States, France, Italy, and Spain will dispatch forces
to join the manoeuvres, aiming at training capabilities of
coordinated fighting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
