<HEADLINE> Ugandans Urged to Report Missing People to Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Ugandans on Wednesday were asked
to report to police the people who may have gone missing since
January this year, especially those believed to have been members
of the cult Movement for the Restoration of Ten commandments of
God.
</P>
<P>
"Arrangements are already in place to ensure that nobody will
either be arrested or inconvenienced after providing such
information," a press release from the police headquarters said.
</P>
<P>
The information will help police estimate the extent of damage
made by the doomsday cult, which is held responsible for the death
of around 1,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Over 530 cult members were burnt to death at Kanungu church in
southwestern Uganda on March 17. Some 400 bodies of murdered cult
members were later exhumed from at least five mass graves.
</P>
</TEXT>
