<HEADLINE> Chittagong Int'l Airport to Go Into Operation in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Minister for Civil
Aviation,Tourism, Housing and Public Works Mosharraf Hossain
Wednesday said the M.A. Hannan International Airport in Chittagong,
the second largest city in Bangladesh, will go into operation in
December.
</P>
<P>
"Arrangement will be made to ply all international flights to
and from the airport by December and the first-ever direct Haj
flight for the people of Chittagong will also be introduced in the
next year,"Hossain said when presiding over a meeting to review
the progress of expansion and modernization of Chittagong airport.
</P>
<P>
The minister said Chittagong airport was being developed into
an international one at a cost of 6 billion taka (115 million U.S.
dollars) as part of Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina's program for
turning the port city into a commercial capital.
</P>
<P>
Hossain said with the internationalization of the airport, the
importance of Chittagong will be immensely enhanced in the fields
of trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
"Head offices of some important government and non-government
establishments will move to Chittagong," he added.
</P>
<P>
Being built over 1,200 acres of land, the airport will have
modern amenities in addition to recreational facilities for the
passengers.
</P>
</TEXT>
