<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Produce Map on Coral Reefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's National Space and
Aviation Agency will finalize work to produce a map on the country
's coral reefs by the end of 2000 as part of a national reef
rehabilitation program.
</P>
<P>
"The map on coral reefs is the initial target of Coremap (Coral
Reef Rehabilitation and Management Program)," said Bidawi Hasyim,
a researcher at the National Atomic Power Agency.
</P>
<P>
He said production of the map is a condition that must be
fulfilled to obtain funds for Coremap's implementation from a
number of international financial organizations, including the
Asian Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The map would be used to draw up a program to rehabilitate and
prevent further damage to the country's coral reefs, Bidawi said.
</P>
<P>
No accurate information is currently available on the total
width of sea bottom covered by coral reefs in Indonesia but it is
believed to be somewhere between 7,500 and 120,000 square
kilometers, according to the researcher.
</P>
<P>
"These figures are mainly hypothetical and not based on
research in the field," he was quoted by the Antara News Agency
Wednesday as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
