<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Starts Construction of Ho Chi Minh Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- A ground breaking ceremony for the
construction of the Ho Chi Minh Highway was held in Bo Trach
district of Vietnam's central province of Quang Binh Wednesday,
according to a report of Vietnam News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The 347-km stretch of the highway in the province will account
for more than a quarter of the total length of the highway, the
second north-south highway in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Ho Chi Minh Highway will connect Hoa Lac village in the
northern province of Ha Tay to Ho Chi Minh City's Binh Phuoc
Crossroads via the historic Ho Chi Minh Trail which was originally
built in 1959.
</P>
<P>
A total investment capital of 5,300 billion Vietnamese dong (
378 million U.S. dollars) will be needed in the first phase to
upgrade 1,094 km of the existing road and build 220 km of new road
which runs through 10 provinces from Ha Tay in the north to the
central highlands province of Kon Tum.
</P>
<P>
The national highway is linked to deep-water ports along the
country's central region to form a communication network
connecting to neighboring countries and ease traffic jams in the
monsoon season.
</P>
<P>
It will play an active role in the planning and reasonable use
of a potential-rich area with some 28 million people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
