<HEADLINE> Canada Gives Aid to Bangladesh for Poverty Reduction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will get over 570 million
taka (11 million U.S. dollars) as a grant from Canada to help
alleviate poverty under a memorandum of understanding (MOU) signed
here Wednesday between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi Secretary of Economic Relations Division of Finance
Ministry Masihur Rahman and Canadian High Commissioner in
Bangladesh David Preston signed the MOU on behalf of their
respective governments, according to a Press Information
Department handout.
</P>
<P>
Under the MOU, Canada will provide a grant of 11 million
dollars over a period of three years.
</P>
<P>
The fund will be given to the Rural Poverty Alleviation
Foundation to strengthen its institutional capacity for
sustainable development and enhance the capacity of the rural poor
and the disadvantaged to contribute to the economic development.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian assistance also aims at enhancing the capacity of
the foundation for effective policy formulation. 
</P>
