<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Members Adopt Proposal to Monitor Madcow Disease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said
Wednesday the EU's Standing Veterinary Committee has adopted a
proposal to reinforce the epidemic surveillance of madcow disease
or BSE.
</P>
<P>
All the 15 EU members have agreed to introduce a monitoring
program from January 1, 2001, under which an annual test will be
carried out on a targeted sample of cattle, with a particular
focus on animals which die on farms, sick animals slaughtered as
emergency and animals displaying behavioral or neurological signs.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, around 65,000 tests will be conducted
among the cattle population at risk. The test results will provide
a more accurate picture of the incidence of BSE in the EU and the
patterns of its infectivity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
