<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Antarctic Expedition Returns to Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese scientific expedition
ship Xuelong (Snow Dragon) docked at the port of Shanghai today,
marking the successful conclusion of its latest voyage to
Antarctica.
</P>
<P>
The Xuelong left the port of Pudong here on November 1 last
year, embarking on China's 16th expedition to the Antarctic
continent since the first expedition was mounted in 1984. The
Xuelong sailed 27,053 nautical miles over a period of 157 days to
reach its destination.
</P>
<P>
The 137 members of the expedition conducted scientific research
projects and supply tasks for China's Antarctic research stations
of Zhongshan and Changcheng.
</P>
<P>
They collected geographical data for relief maps of 64
Antarctic islands and 110 sq km of the continent.
</P>
<P>
One of the most important findings was a yellow earth-like
substance which proved to be ancient soil, found in an ice gorge.
</P>
<P>
The team also collected 28 samples of aerolite and an abundance
of ice and snow samples, which it is expected will provide a
deeper understanding of global climate changes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000405.0066 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Power Cooperation Agreement Signed at Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the 2000 Investment and Trade Fair for Cooperation between
East and West China, which opened here yesterday, the 100-year-old
Meiya Power Co. Ltd and the Shaanxi-based Jingbian Natural Gas
Power Plant of the China Zhenglian-Sanbei Group agreed to
construct two generator sets with natural gas as the fuel. The
capacity of the generators will be 300,000 kw each.
</P>
<P>
Eric D'Esparbes, deputy chief financial officer of the Meiya
Power Co. Ltd, said that the company has set up two power plants
in northwest China's Gansu Province, and the plant in Shaanxi will
go into operation within three years.
</P>
<P>
The northern part of Shaanxi, which borders Gansu Province and
the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, has an estimated 500 billion cu
m of natural gas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
