<DOCNO> XIE20000405.0073 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Firmer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
firmer Wednesday after a Reserve Bank of Australia interest rate
hike.
</P>
<P>
The central bank tightened monetary policy for the third time
in five months Wednesday, raising its cash rate target to 5.75
percent, from 5.50 percent.
</P>
<P>
At the close Australian dollar was at 60.54 U.S. cents, from 60.
26 at Tuesday's close.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar fell sharply in the past two months in
the face of a strengthening world economy, which ordinarily would
be expected to put upward pressure on the exchange rate.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 0.6299 euro from 0.6296 Tuesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
