<HEADLINE> Export Promotion Meeting Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 5 (Xinhua) -- A three-day export promotion
meeting opened here Wednesday, with the participation of more than
400 representatives from 34 countries.
</P>
<P>
The meeting aims at seeking more foreign markets for Nepali
products, promoting tourism and attracting foreign investment in
the country, according to the Nepali Ministry of Industry and
Commerce, the organizer of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
It is also expected to assist the government in formulating
national economic strategies at a time when it is seeking to join
the World Trade Organization and the South Asia Free Trade Area,
the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is coupled with a five-day trade fair with some 60
types of products ranging from carpets to handicrafts and
industrial items, in addition to tourism and banking services.
</P>
<P>
Cultural programs, a traditional Nepalese fashion show and
interactions among buyers and sellers will add to the attractions
of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Besides Nepal, the participants come from Australia, Canada,
China, Japan, Russia, the United States and some other countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
