<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai
on Wednesday felicitates Yoshiro Mori's inauguration as the new
Prime Minister of Japan.
</P>
<P>
In a letter from Chuan's office, the prime minister expressed "
sincere congratulations" to his new Japanese counterpart.
</P>
<P>
Chuan also expressed his hope that Yoshiro Mori's government
will play an important role in Southeastern Asian affairs as its
predecessor did.
</P>
<P>
Yoshiro Mori was sworn in as Japan's new premier Wednesday
after former Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi suffered a massive stroke
and had to be kept on life support.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the move is not expected to bring big changes to
Japan's policy.
</P>
<P>
Mori said he will stick to Obuchi's course, and his cabinet is
the same as the former one except the top post change. 
