<HEADLINE> Duncan Named NBA Player of the Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 5 (Xinhua) -- San Antonio Spurs' center Tim
Duncan was named the National Basketball Association's Player of
the Week from March 27 to April 2.
</P>
<P>
Duncan, who led the Spurs to three wins and one loss during the
span, averaged 26.2 points, 15.3 rebounds, 3.8 assists and 3.25
blocks. He shot .541 in the field during his 43.3 averaging
playing time.
</P>
<P>
He scored 30 points and grabbed 18 rebounds, and was 14-20 in
the field in Spurs' 90-82 win over the Seattle Supersonics on
Monday, and continued to collected 36 points, 15 boards and three
blocks to help Spurs beat the Portland Blazers 89-85 on the second
night.
</P>
<P>
Back to home court on Thursday, Duncan contributed 19 points,
17 rebounds and six blocks for a 102-90 victory over the Golden
State Warriors.
</P>
<P>
The Spurs lost on Sunday to the Miami Heats 88-84 when Duncan
chipped in 19 points, 11 boards and added three blocks.
</P>
<P>
Duncan averaged 12.5 rebounds (ranked third in the league), 2.
23 blocks (seventh) and 23.2 points (tenth) in the season.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for the award were Anthony Mason of the
Charlotte Hornets, Michael Finley of the Dallas Mavericks, Antonio
McDyess and Nick Van Exel of the Denver Nuggets, Ray Allen and San
Cassell of the Milwaukee Bucks, Charles "Bo" Outlaw of the Orlando
Magics, Rodney Rogers of the Phoenix Suns and Karl Malone of the
Utah Jazz. 
</P>
