March 13 and at Washington on March 16), becoming the first Laker
to scored wire-to-wire 40 points or over since Jerry West in 1970.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers (63-12) recorded 15-1 run in March to lead the
National Basketball Association.
</P>
<P>
O'Neal won the monthly award in November and December this
season. He was the scoring leader with 29.1 points averaging and
topped the league on the field goals percentage (.573).
</P>
<P>
He was also ranked second in rebounding (13.7 averaging) and
third in blocking (3.11).
</P>
