<HEADLINE> Yantai Development Zone Reports Fast Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Yantai Economic and
Technological Development Zone, a major state-level development
zone in the city of Yantai in east China's Shandong Province, has
maintained an annual growth rate of 54 percent on average over the
past 15 years, with gross domestic product reaching 3.71 billion
yuan in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Local experts attributed the upward trend mainly to the
development of high-tech industries in the zone.
</P>
<P>
During the past few years, investors from more than 20 foreign
countries, including the United States, Japan, Germany and the
Republic of Korea, have opened 805 businesses in the zone, with a
total investment of 2.71 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
These businesses have helped the zone build information
technology, pharmaceuticals, chemicals, and automotive parts and
components into pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics show that these enterprises have
contributed 80 percent of the zone's total industrial output.
</P>
<P>
Local analysts predict that the zone will keep up its rapid
development momentum in the years to come as more high-tech
projects are introduced to the zone. 
</P>
