help small and medium enterprises (SMEs) improve profitability and
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
"SMEs are a major business sector accounting for 98 percent of
total establishments in Hong Kong and 60 percent of the work force.
They have been a major contributing force to Hong Kong's economic
development," said John Steward, American Express' vice president
and general manager for Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"With growing everyday business expenses and expected increased
engagement in Internet and China business travel activities, it is
more important than ever for SMEs to exercise better cost control
and management of their expenses. The American Express Business
Card is dedicated to serving these needs," he said at the launch
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The Business Card, a charge card without pre-set spending limit,
is customized for owners and executives of SMEs with 100 or fewer
employees.
</P>
<P>
The card offers a unique "Business Savings Program" that can
enhance SMEs' competitiveness by helping them reduce costs in
three areas -- day-to-day business expenses, e-commerce and
business travel to the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Steward expressed optimism about the market potential of its
Business Card and said cardholders can save manpower and
administrative time in dealing with their suppliers.
</P>
<P>
American Express is a diversified worldwide travel, financial
services and network services company. Founded in 1850, it is a
leader in charge and credit cards, Traveler Cheques, travel,
financial planning, investment products, insurance and
international banking. 
