<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drought Hits Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Wheat output will probably
decline by a wide margin this year in Henan Province, a major
grain producer in central China, if the current drought continues.
</P>
<P>
Drought is hitting 1.37 million hectares of wheat at present,
which is a key period to the growth of the crop.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said that 3,800 hectares of wheat in the province
already have seriously withered.
</P>
<P>
From January to March, Henan reported only 7.82 mm of rainfall,
87 percent less than normal. Most parts in the province have had
no rainfall for nearly 60 days now.
</P>
<P>
Nearly one million people in the area, and livestock are also
having difficulty getting water, as more than 200 small and medium-
sized reservoirs have run dry.
</P>
<P>
Authorities note that the drought situation is expected to
remain serious for the near future.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
