<HEADLINE> HSI Plunges 3.4 Pct on Wall Street Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed
Wednesday's session at 16,318.44 points, down 3.4 percent, or 574.
49 points, following a 1.77-percent slide of the U.S. Nasdaq on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Investors sold off blue chips and tech stocks and sought refuge
in banks and utilities.
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of the benchmark Hang Seng Index, both
Finance and Utilities picked up 1.09 percent while Properties and
Commerce and Industries shed 1.72 percent and 6.24 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 16.297 billion HK dollars (2.089 billion U.S.
dollars), compared with Monday's 10.657 billion HK dollars (1.366
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China Enterprises Index went down 4.47 percent and
the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporation Index lost 9.59 percent.
</P>
<P>
The index opened lower at 16,599.07, down 293.86 points, or 1.
74 percent and closed the morning session at 16,526.19, down 2.17
percent or 366.74 points. 
