<HEADLINE> China Digital Library Project Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Participants at a conference on
China's Digital Library Project, which was held here today,
announced that the project has been officially launched after
years of preparations.
</P>
<P>
Government officials and experts from 21 units involved in the
project attended the meeting, at which some prominent experts and
scholars were appointed members of an advisory committee to guide
the project.
</P>
<P>
Digital libraries are electronic data bases for storing and
utilizing knowledge and information, emerging along with the
development of Internet technology.
</P>
<P>
Currently, English-language information dominates the Internet,
while Chinese-language information makes up less than one percent
of the world's total.
</P>
<P>
The creation of the China Digital Library is aimed at
increasing the use of Chinese-language information and promoting
the Chinese culture, the experts noted.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, local experts have conducted a series of
research projects related to the digital library, as the country
is now capable of building this important new storehouse of
culture and information.  
</P>
</TEXT>
