<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Law Society Marks Anniversary of Dong Biwu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The China Law Society held a forum
here today to mark the 25th anniversary of the death of Dong Biwu
(1886-1975), one of the founders of the Communist Party of China (
CPC) and an important trailblazer in the field of law for the
People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Attending the forum were Ren Jianxin, a vice chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) and chairman of the law society, and Luo Haocai,
a CPPCC National Committee vice chairman and a vice president of
the Supreme People's Court.
</P>
<P>
As a young man, Dong studied law in Japan and became a leading
official in charge of legal affairs in CPC-led revolutionary bases.
After 1949, when the People's Republic of China was founded, Dong
held a number of important positions including vice premier-cum-
chairman of the Politics and Law Committee, president of the
Supreme People's Court, vice chairman of the Standing Committee of
the National People's Congress, and acting state president.
</P>
</TEXT>
