<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Internet Subscribers on Rapid Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's Multimedia
Development Corporation (MDC) Wednesday predicted that about 1.4
million Internet subscribers in the country are expected to
register by the end of this year against 778,000 at the end of
1999.
</P>
<P>
MDC Executive Chairman Othman Yeop Abdullah said in Petaling
Jaya near here that like last year, about 25 percent of the
subscribers are expected to come from the corporate sector.
</P>
<P>
In tandem with the anticipated rise in the number of Internet
subscribers, the number of Internet users in Malaysia is expected
to increase to between 6 million and 7 million by the end of this
year, he said, adding, "For each subscriber, there are normally
four or five users (getting access to the Internet), so you can
time 1.4 million subscribers by four or five."
</P>
<P>
He said the number of Malaysian Internet users who buy online
is also rapidly increasing, with total revenue from e-commerce
activities in Malaysia estimated at 187 million ringgit (49.21
million U.S. dollars) last year from 68 million ringgit (17.894
million dollars) for 1998.
</P>
<P>
The figure is expected to roughly double every year and reach
some 6 billion ringgit (1.578 billion dollars) by the year 2003.
</P>
</TEXT>
