<BODY>
<HEADLINE> KFOR, Serbs Clash in Kosovo, 32 Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 5 (Xinhua) -- KFOR troops clashed with Serb
residents in southern Kosovo on Tuesday, during which 16 KFOR
soldiers and as many Serbs were injured, the Tanjug news agency
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the local radio as saying that a detachment
of the international police force and KFOR's U.S. troops arrived
at Sevce village in southern Kosovo at noon, claiming they were on
a mission to search for stolen property, and arrested a young Serb
man on charges of "war crimes."
</P>
<P>
More than 3,500 local Serbs blocked the roads and demanded the
immediate release of the young man and stop of searching.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. soldiers fired rubber bullets and tear gas and set
police dogs to disperse the crowd. The Serbs fought back with rods
and hoes and seized the young man back during the melee, said the
report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
