<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ferdinand Issues Quit Threat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 5 (Xinhua) -- English premier league soccer club
West Ham's Rio Ferdinand has hinted he could quit Upton Park next
season unless the club starts challenging for a trophy.
</P>
<P>
The England defender admitted he was disappointed at the
Hammers form this season and warned that if the club sells any of
their top players it will hasten his departure.
</P>
<P>
"If the club wants to go forward, selling players can't happen,
" he said. "It's as simple as that. If it does, I'm off."
</P>
<P>
"I thought we had a really good chance of winning something
this season. Next year we've got to do it. We've been promising to
for three or four years, but we've under-achieved. It's no good
bringing through all these young players if we don't win something.
I've made no secret of the fact that I would like to play abroad
one day, to experience life in another country," he told New
Nation magazine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
