<HEADLINE> Polish Embassy Celebrates Anniversary of Six-Century-Old University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua)-- A reception given by the Polish
embassy here today marked the 600th anniversary of the renovation
of the nation's academic jewel, Jagiellonian University.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Jizhong, professor of Eastern European languages at
Beijing Foreign Studies University and author of a book on the
university, said in a speech that Jagiellonian University has a
great and honorable tradition of democratic academic thought and
consistent reform.
</P>
<P>
The university, founded by King Kazimierz the Great in 1364,
was the second university ever founded in the Slavic ethnic region,
and was also among the first universities in Europe.
</P>
<P>
After suffering a decline following King Kazimierz's death, it
was renovated in 1400 with the support of King Jagiello and Queen
Jadwiga. It assumed the name of the king in 1818.
</P>
<P>
The university came to be one of the cultural and academic
centers of Europe in the mid-16th century, and the great
Renaissance scientist Nicolaus Copernicus was among its
distinguished students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
