<HEADLINE> "Health for All" Project Launched in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Primary Hygiene Fund of China
launched its Health-for-All Project here today, aimed at providing
medical services to poor villagers living in underdeveloped
western areas.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zhenghua, vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), attended today's opening
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of health-care vehicles will be sent to the western
provinces and ethnic autonomous regions, according to officials
with the fund.
</P>
<P>
The project will help local villagers reduce the cost of
medical treatment and improve the services at rural clinics.
</P>
<P>
In the backward western region, local villagers have been
suffering from both poverty and illness, which are mutually
related, the experts said. In some remote areas, it is very
difficult for villagers to get to a hospital and receive proper
treatment, they noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
