<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish Parliament to Meet on Constitutional Change </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Turkish parliament is to meet again
Wednesday afternoon to vote on a government-proposed constitutional
amendment package, which is billed as the last chance for the
president to stay in office for another term.
</P>
<P>
The package, initiated and pushed hard by Prime Minister Bulent
Ecevit, got only 303 "yes" votes in the first round of voting last
Wednesday, far fewer than the minimum 330 votes required for the
bill to be legislated.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit has repeated on several occasions after the voting that
he wants the 76-year-old President Suleyman Demirel, whose single
seven-year term is to end on May, to serve another five-year term
for the sake of the country's good, describing Demirel as a "
guarantee of stability."
</P>
<P>
If the bill garners enough votes in the second round of secret
balloting, Demirel can be re-nominated as a presidential candidate
during the candidacy period of April 16-26, thus becoming the most
likely candidate to assume office.
</P>
<P>
However, if the bill still fails to get the backing of the
parliament, the search for a new candidate will begin and the
coalition partners will be faced with a different scenario.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the ruling three-party coalition reached an agreement
at Monday's summit on monitoring ballot casting by deputies during
the second round.
</P>
<P>
The poor voting last Wednesday, which triggered a confidence
crisis on Ecevit's government, was mainly attributed to the
defections by some deputies despite they had promised to vote for
Demirel beforehand.
</P>
<P>
Under the current constitution, a minimum of 330 votes in the
550-member parliament are required for the approval of any
constitutional amendment.
</P>
<P>
A total of 367 votes are a must for the amendment package to be
adopted by the parliament. If the number of votes remains somewhere
in between 330 and 367, a referendum will be attached to the
procedure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
