ended a landmark two-day summit in Cairo, pledging more economic
cooperation and agreeing to convene again after three years in
Europe. The Africa-EU Summit voiced concern over Africa's 350-
billion-U.S.-dollar debt burden, compared with 110 billion dollars
in 1980. 
