<DOCNO> XIE20000405.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Discovers Large Gas Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Oil Minister Bijan Namdar
Zanganeh announced on Wednesday that the country has discovered a
large gas field with a reserve of more than 445 billion cubic
meters of gas and over 240 million barrels of liquid gas.
</P>
<P>
Zanganeh said that the Tabnak gas field with an value of about
16.5 billion U.S. dollars was discovered in the southern Fars
province by the National Iranian Oil Exploration Company (NIOEC),
the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The exploration work started in 1998 and so far the drilling
reached 2,245 meters deep with a cost of 30 billion rials (about 10
million dollars at the official rate), he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that Iran has drafted a 30-year exploitation
plan for the field and the production would start in the second
half of the current Iranian calendar year starting March 20.
</P>
<P>
He said that the daily production would be 1.5 billion to 2
million cubic feet or 40.5 million to 54 million cubic meters of
natural gas and 24,000 to 32,000 barrels of liquid gas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
