<HEADLINE> Singapore Unveils Strategies for Infocomm Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Singapore has mapped out
strategies for developing its information and telecommunications
industry as the next major sector of growth.
</P>
<P>
"We want to position Singapore as a leading infocomm hub in the
Asia-Pacific for telecommunications services, e-business
transactions and distribution of digital goods and services,"
Minister for Communications and Information Technology Yeo Cheow
Tong said at the opening ceremony of an information technology (IT)
exhibition here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The three strategies to achieve the goal include jump-starting
the interactive broadband multimedia, building new capabilities
and leveraging on innovation in key growth areas and fostering
strategic partnerships and alliances overseas.
</P>
<P>
The strategies are the latest of a series of Infocomm 21
announcements made by the minister since last January.
</P>
<P>
The first was on the liberalization of the telecom market,
followed by strategies to help Singaporeans go online and attract
infocomm manpower and talent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
