<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pyongyang-Shenyang Air Route Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 5 (Xinhua) -- An air route from Pyongyang to
Shenyang, capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province, opened
today.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said that an Air Koryo aircraft took off from the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and landed at
Shenyang's Taoxian International Airport at 10:30 a.m. today.
</P>
<P>
This is the second air route opened by DPRK carriers in China,
following the Pyongyang-Beijing route that became operational in
1959.
</P>
<P>
The new air route will have two flights a week, on Wednesday
and Saturday, and the flight will take one and a half hours.
</P>
<P>
DPRK aviation officials said the new route will become another
bridge to deepen the friendship between the peoples of the two
countries, and will further consolidate cooperation between the
civil aviation departments of China and the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
Taoxian airport now has six regular international air routes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
