<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Lower Against U.S. Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian rupiah exchange rate
against U.S. dollar on Wednesday declined to 7,800 per U.S. dollar
from 7,500 early this week due to the slow pace of economic
reforms.
</P>
<P>
Some dealers even predicted that the rupiah will plunge to 8,
000 per dollar, if the working of the economic ministers does not
improve.
</P>
<P>
At the end of last month, the rupiah exchange rate against U.S.
dollar showed signs of weakening, following news that the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) would delay its aid to Indonesia
due to the government failure in implementing the economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
The reforms focus on bank and corporate restructuring programs.
</P>
<P>
Talking to reporters before attending Cabinet meeting here
Wednesday, Governor of the Central Bank Syahril Sabirin was
optimistic that the rupiah will recover and strengthen again if
the government is successful in implementing a set of delayed key
reforms by the new April 8 deadline agreed with the IMF.
</P>
<P>
He said that the rupiah exchange rate against U.S. dollar could
go back to the level of 7,000 per dollar.
</P>
<P>
"If the deadline of April 8 is met (by the government), that
will be able to strengthen the rupiah," he added.
</P>
<P>
Sabirin also said that the rupiah also could recover if the
country is successful in asking for debt rescheduling from the
donor countries in the upcoming donors meeting.
</P>
<P>
The donor countries grouping in the Consultatives Group on
Indonesia (CGI) is due to meet in Paris on April 10-12, under
which Indonesia will ask for debt rescheduling of its foreign loan
mounting to 2.1 billion U.S. dollars for the April-December 2000
fiscal year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
