<DOCNO> XIE20000405.0197 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Largest Carbon Single Crystal Developed In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The largest single crystal of
Carbon 60 (C60) numerator, 1.3 centimeters at its widest, has been
developed by scientists at Zhejiang University in Hangzhou,
capital of east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Previously, the widest part of the largest single C60 crystal
in the world was only six mm.
</P>
<P>
The Institute of Condensed-Matter Physics attached to the
Department of Physics of Zhejiang University used a gas phase
method to develop this largest C60 single crystal in the world.
</P>
<P>
The C60 round numerator is a fine photo-conductivity and
lubricant material with super-conductive characteristics under low
temperatures when compounded with kalium and other metals, experts
explained.
</P>
<P>
Some experts claim that the development of this crystal is the
most important achievement in fullerene research following the
single-walled carbon nanotube in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
