<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Marital Relations Diversified in 21st Century: Experts (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Since the early eighties, there
have been fundamental changes in marriage and family relations in
China, following the economic development and social progess.
</P>
<P>
 In an interview with Xinhua, Chen Xinxin, a well-known
marriage and family expert with the All-China Women's Federation
said that in the next 100 years, "Marriages and family all over
the world will be more diversified, men and women will be more
independent, and individual rights of family members will be
better respected."
</P>
<P>
In urban areas, she said, 60 percent of families only have
three to four members. This figure is expected to rise. More
people will marry and have children much later.
</P>
<P>
The number of single people will increase and more of them will
prefer not to have any children, she added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000405.0203 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Marital Relations Diversified in 21st Century: Experts (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Economic factors will play a lesser role in choosing a spouse
or partner, while people will pay more attention to how they will
get along, she said.
</P>
<P>
There will be less household chores with the more electrical
and smarter appliances, she said, adding family quarrels over
household chores will be less.
</P>
<P>
Higher education and more knowledge may increase people's
expectations over marriage and love, and may lead to more
misfortune, misery, and thus more divorces, she warned.
</P>
<P>
Chen stated that divorce agreements and trial divorces will be
more opted for and divorce rate will be up.
</P>
<P>
The society will be more tolerant with ultra-marital affairs,
and people's responsibility for marriage and family will come more
from self-reflection, self-discipline and self-redress than from
social pressure, she said.
</P>
<P>
With relaxation of control over people's personal affairs, more
ultra-marital affairs will appear, she predicted.
</P>
<P>
People's freedom of marriage from social pressure will increase
considerably, more will opt not to marry, and the number of single-
parent families will increase, the expert said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000405.0204 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Marital Relations Diversified in 21st Century: Experts (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
However, she said, they will face strong opposition from the
traditional forces which stress on parental agreement on marriage
matters.
</P>
<P>
Early marriages and births will decrease along with the rise of
women's social status, improvement of rural economy and
establishment of a pension system, she said.
</P>
<P>
Because of poverty and maladjusted ratio of men and women, a
considerable number of male population will find it difficult to
find a wife, she warned.
</P>
<P>
Divorce will still be difficult, especially when involving the
separation of farmland, care of children, she said, noting that
women working in factories will have more say in this matter.
</P>
<P>
Extra-marital affairs will mean both a temptation and danger
for rural women, which will lead to turbulent life or even tragedy
for them, she concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
