<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australia Raises Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Australian Reserve Bank
Wednesday lifted interest rates by a quarter of a percentage point
to 5.75 percent, from 5.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The bank said inflationary concerns over the medium term,
rather than the current strength of the economy, was behind its
decision to increase interest rates.
</P>
<P>
This is the third time in five months that the central bank has
tightened its monetary policy. In February, the bank raised the
interest rate by 0.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
A further rise in the coming months is expected.
</P>
<P>
An economist was quoted by AAP as saying, "There are inflation
risks from the tightening labor market, stronger global growth and
domestic growth, the Australian dollar in its depressed state
would also be a consideration."
</P>
<P>
Inflationary pressure is evident in some sectors, such as wages,
household credit and oil prices, Australian analysts pointed out.
</P>
<P>
However, Treasurer Peter Costello warned Wednesday against any
lenders raising interest rates by more than 0.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
"There are no grounds for any bank or other home lender to move
their rates up by more than 0.25 percent and I will be watching
them very, very carefully, I can assure you of that," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000405.0215 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Inflation Rate Picks Up in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Year-on-year inflation rate in the
Philippines rose to 3.3 percent in March from 3 percent in
February,although it was lower than the 8.7 percent in March 1999,
the National Statistics Office said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the office, higher prices of items in all
commodity groups contributed to the increase in the inflation rate.
</P>
<P>
The rates for food, beverages and tobacco went up to 0.7
percent in March from a negative 0.6 percent in February while
those for fuel, light and water jumped to 9.2 percent from 9
percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, inflation in services remained at the February rate
of 11.4 percent, the office said.
</P>
<P>
By region, the inflation rate for the national capital area
increased from 2.8 percent in February to 3.2 percent in March,
the highest in the region since October last year.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the inflation rate in areas outside the
capital region went up to 3.4 percent in March from 3.1 percent in
the previous month.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank of the Philippines said earlier that it would
keep the country's interest rate unchanged if the inflation rate
was below 4 percent in March.
</P>
<P>
The country's overnight borrowing rate now stands at 8.75
percent while the overnight lending rate is 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
Labor and Employment Secretary Blenvenido Laguesma reassured
the public that the government will continue to explore ways to
keep prices of basic commodities stable and inflation from
shooting up.
</P>
<P>
For the whole of 1999, the country's inflation rate averaged 6.
6 percent, mainly due to the agriculture sector's remarkable
turnaround which grew by 6.5 percent in the year.
</P>
<P>
The government has set an inflation target of 6 to 7 percent
for 2000, a goal most analysts believe is achievable. 
</P>
</TEXT>
