 considering various strict measures to deal with public
demonstrations until the completion of the general elections in
May.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that more than 120 people were arrested last
weekend in almost 40 cases of recent political violence. Two
people were killed and 100 others injured in cases ranging from
assaults, malicious injury to property, theft, public violence and
murder. Property worth millions of U.S. dollars was damaged.
