<HEADLINE> Old Industrial Base Reports Favorable Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning, an industrial base in
northeast China, has reported favorable growth in its industrial
sector during the first two months of the year.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that the sales in state-run and non-
state enterprises with an annual sales income of more than five
million yuan soared by 20.6 percent during the January-February
period, with the production-to-sales ratio reaching 94.5 percent,
2.8 percentage points higher than the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Eleven cities out of a total of 14 cities in Liaoning province
registered double-digit growth. And seven cities recorded
industrial growth of more than 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
The state sector recorded a 9.6 percent rise in output value
and an increase of 22.1 percent in sales.
</P>
<P>
Industrial output of FAW-Jinbei Co. Ltd, an automobile giant,
increased by 130.8 percent or 500 million yuan during the two-
month period, accounting for 85.2 percent of total industrial
output in Shenyang.
</P>
<P>
Provincial officials attribute the favorable growth to the
furthering of the state enterprise reform and efforts to increase
profitability.
</P>
<P>
The officials are optimistic about a comparatively fast
economic growth rate of the industrial sector of the province for
the first half of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
