<HEADLINE> Holiday Inn Downtown leads Hotels In Room Occupancy Rate in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Holiday Inn Downtown Beijing was
recently announced by the Beijing Tourism Bureau to top the
ranking of hotel room occupancy rate among tourism hotels in
Beijing for 1999.
</P>
<P>
The hotel has topped the ranking for eight years in a row,
since it became one of the Holiday Inn's chains in 1992. Its
averaged hotel room occupancy rate stood above 85 percent in the
1992-1999 period.
</P>
<P>
"Holiday Inn's brandname attraction and its management
mechanism have played an indispensable role for the success," said
Yang Shaohua, the hotel president.
</P>
<P>
The Holiday Inn has a chain of over 2,400 hotels in some 60
countries. Its parent company, Bass Plc, owns another two luxury
hotel chains, Inter-Continental and Crown Plaza hotel chains. Bass
is currently expanding its hotel network in the Asia-Pacific
region. The Holiday Inn now has 25 chains in China.
</P>
<P>
The four-star rank hotel in Beijing with 346 rooms earned 80
million yuan from sales last year. The net profit amounted to 25
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Hu Minkang, general manager of the hotel, expressed his hope
that China should build its own hotel conglomerates. He said that
Jianguo Hotel in Beijing and White Swan Hotel in Guangzhou are
making such endeavor to establish a unique management style in
preparations for expansion. However, they are still at an initial
stage.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1998, the number of tourist hotels in China had
totaled 5,728 with nearly 250 of them being luxury hotels. In
Beijing alone, there are some 50 luxury hotels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
