<HEADLINE> 87th China Export Commodities Fair Goes Online </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The 87th China Export
Commodities Fair will be brought to the Internet at a new website
address: eastran.com.
</P>
<P>
the China Export Commodities Fair is a biannual event held in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province. Each fair
lasts for 15 days, and the 87th fair will open on April 15.
</P>
<P>
Information from the Guangdong Provincial Bureau of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation explains that the on-line service
will facilitate companies that can not attend the fair to take
part via the 'net.
</P>
<P>
In addition to presenting general information about the fair,
the bureau will open a great number of specialized markets and
exhibitions on-line in cooperation with localities that produce
particular commodities of the best quality.
</P>
<P>
By now, many import and export companies from across the
country, as well as overseas commercial organizations in Guangzhou
representing countries including the United States, Germany, Japan,
the Republic of Korea and Italy have registered to open on-line
booths under the specially opened website address.
</P>
<P>
A record of over 12.7 billion U.S. dollars worth of export
deals were concluded at the 86th China Export Commodities Fair
held last autumn. 
</P>
