<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Chinese Insurance Agents Penalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Two professional insurance agents
have been penalized by the China Insurance Regulatory Commission (
CIRC), ordering them to close temporarily for three months.
</P>
<P>
According to the CIRC, the Beijing Anbang Insurance Agent Co.
has been penalized for registering under another name other than
the one approved by the CIRC. The Company was also found to have
false registered capital and bad management.
</P>
<P>
The Guizhou Hong'an Insurance Agent Co. has been penalized for
changing its name, its chairman and manager without CIRC approval.
</P>
<P>
The two companies violated relevant provisions as provided by
the China's Insurance Law and administrative regulations on
insurance agents, the CIRC said.
</P>
<P>
Both companies were among the first group of professional
insurance agents approved by the CIRC late last year.
</P>
<P>
CIRC said that China's insurance intermediary market will
develop enormously in the next five years and become an important
part of the insurance market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
