<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China-made Down Jackets Report Good Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- China has become a major exporter
of down jackets, and these products have achieved relatively good
quality, according to a recent random examination.
</P>
<P>
The spot check, conducted by the State Bureau of Quality and
Technical Supervision (SBQTS) among 74 producers of down products
across China, show that 78.4 percent met state standards, and all
the down jackets produced by large state-owned enterprises were
qualified.
</P>
<P>
China's production of down products began in the mid-1970s, and
since then has witnessed rapid development. Currently, China has
more than 1,600 down jacket manufacturers, and among these over
100 are engaged in large-scale production.
</P>
<P>
China-made down jackets are exported to the United States,
Japan, and Europe.
</P>
<P>
However, the examination found some problems in the products
made by private enterprises, which were urged by the SBQTS to
improve product quality.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
