<DOCNO> XIE20000405.0238 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Desertification Due To Increased Dust Storms in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Meteorological experts point out
that the desertification of northwestern China is the major cause
of increased dust storms in north China this spring.
</P>
<P>
They said strong winds were not the "chief cause" of four dust
storms over the past month in Beijing and other part of north
China as some people believed.
</P>
<P>
Desertification prevention experts from the State Forestry
Administration said that though Beijing and Tianjin have made
enormous efforts in planting trees and vegetation, worsening
desertification in northwest China has posed threats of dust
storms to the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
In Zhangjiakou, Hebei, a province neighboring Beijing, several
deserts blow nearly one million tons of sand to Beijing each year.
</P>
<P>
An official with the State Forestry Administration said China
will accelerate afforestation in Inner Mongolia plateau and build
three big forestry farms in Hebei Province to form a "green
shelter" for Beijing and Tianjin. The dust storm that swept
through Beijing in late March killed three construction workers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000405.0239 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quality of China's Gas Water Heaters Improved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The quality of China's gas-fired
water heaters, which have caused many accidents every year, have
been greatly improved, according to a recent random examination.
</P>
<P>
The spot check, conducted by the State Bureau Quality and
Technical Supervision (SBQTS) among 57 gas water heater producers
across China, showed that 87.7 percent met standards.
</P>
<P>
The check found that 100 percent of the water heaters produced
by large enterprises were up to state standards, better than the
qualification rate for medium and small-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Currently, a total of 183 producers of gas water heaters have
gained production licenses, and more then 30 million gas water
heaters are in use among Chinese families.
</P>
<P>
Quality problems including inferior materials and component
parts were found in small manufacturers, which were urged by the
SBQTS to improve the quality of their products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
