<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Representatives from over 40
Australian educational organizations will gather in China this
weekend to host the 2000 Australian Education Exhibition, designed
to introduce more Chinese to the Australian system of higher
education.
</P>
<P>
The Expo will be held from April 7 to 9 at the Great Wall Hotel
in Beijing and is sponsored by the China Education Association for
International Exchange (CEAIE) and the Australian embassy.
</P>
<P>
