Expo is the largest exhibition on Australian education in China
and many first-rate Australian education organizations will be
attending.
</P>
<P>
The Expo is an important part of the "2000 Australian Education
Fair" which is to be held in Beijing and Shanghai at the same time.
</P>
<P>
You noted that CEAIE and the Australian University President
Commission will hold the Sino-Australian university president
seminar in Shanghai on April 13, focusing on scientific management
and university scientific parks.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, over 10,000 students from China's mainland are
studying in Australia. Last year, the Australian embassy issued
over 4,000 visas for students to study in Australia. The number is
expected to reach 6,000 this year. 
</P>
