<DOCNO> XIE20000405.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Largest U.S. Bank to Deliver Online Financial Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Bank of America, the largest
bank in the United States, said Tuesday that it is teaming with e-
business software maker Ariba to create an Internet-based
financial marketplace to provide financial services.
</P>
<P>
The online services include payment, financing, wire transfers
and purchasing services. The financial firm will use Ariba
technology to build Bank of America Marketplace, a new company
that will launch and run the business-to-business (B2B)
marketplace for the bank's 2 million business customers.
</P>
<P>
Bank of America said the marketplace will provide electronic
invoicing, extensive payments capabilities and a foreign money
exchange. The alliance will gather the bank's roughly 7 billion U.
S. dollars in yearly worldwide purchasing from outside suppliers
and streamline its procurement process.
</P>
<P>
"The digital space needs more financial capabilities," the bank
said in a statement. "The B2B market is greatly outpacing the
online credit card payment market. With this alliance we will try
and meet these financial needs and others."
</P>
<P>
The number of online marketplaces has been growing rapidly in
the United States over the past four weeks. Last month, the Big
Three U.S. automakers of General Motors, Ford and DiamlerChrysler,
as well as Toyota, Nissan and Fiat, jointly announced a B2B
integrated supplier exchange through a single portal.
</P>
<P>
About the same time, four of the world's largest aerospace and
defense companies -- Boeing, Lockheed Martin, Raytheon and British
Aerospace -- also said that they would connect industry suppliers
and buyers via the Internet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
