<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Diplomats and representatives of
foreign enterprises in Beijing from over 20 European and Asian
countries visited northwest China's Gansu Province recently,
accompanied by Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation Zhang Xiang.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Governor of Gansu Province Guo Kun told the visitors that
the province is currently restructuring its economy and enhancing
infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture, and infrastructure construction in energy and
transportation and communication are the priority areas the
province encourages for foreign investment, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also encouraged foreign businesses to invest in the
processing of mineral products, chemical products production, and
service industries such as insurance and tourism.  
</P>
