<HEADLINE> China Strengthens Quarantine Against Italian Bird Epidemic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- China has recently called for
strengthening the precautions against the possible importation of
infected birds and related products from Italy.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic of bird diseases that broke out in Italy last
December has become more serious over the past few months,
according to an official with the State Administration for Entry-
Exit Inspection and Quarantine (SAEEIQ).
</P>
<P>
Approximately seven million birds were found infected in Italy
so far, he said.
</P>
<P>
Such an incident is rare in terms of both the number of bird
species involved and the number of infected birds, the SAEEIQ
official noted. 
</P>
