<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Launches Digital Information Project for Land Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- China has launched a digital
information project for land resources to push forward the
assessment and monitoring of land.
</P>
<P>
The project includes construction of a basic data bank for
China's land, mineral, and other resources, a land resources
management information system, and social service systems.
Information technology for investigating and assessing land
resources will be developed, and a nationwide information network
will be created.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Ministry of Land Resources said this
project is expected to be completed by 2002, and after the
completion, authoritative land resources information will be
available on the network.
</P>
<P>
In addition, China is pushing forward the creation of Digital
Earth, a process through which any geographical location on earth
can be digitized and made available on the Internet for either
economic or military use.
</P>
<P>
Digital Earth also can provide rich information for mineral,
and oil and natural gas exploration, and conserving forests,
grasslands, and ocean resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
