<HEADLINE> UNICEF to Help Welfare of Pakistani Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Children's
Fund (UNICEF) has pledged to provide 92 million U.S. dollars to
help improve the welfare of Pakistani children, according to a
press release available here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Saving the lives of 125,000 young children annually and putting
600,000 more girls in primary schools in the country are just two
of the goals of the master plan of the operations agreed on
Tuesday by the Pakistani government and UNICEF, the press release
said.
</P>
<P>
Major areas of the plan include child health, water and
environmental sanitation, basic education, women's health,
nutrition, child rights, advocacy and communication, planning
monitoring and evaluation and the focus district program as well
as cross sectoral support. 
