<HEADLINE> 12 People Killed in Police-Guerrilla Clashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people were killed on
Monday in two separate clashes between police and the ultra-
leftist guerrillas in mid-western Nepal, according to reports
reaching here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The reports said seven guerrillas were killed on Monday when
they exchanged fire with the police in Maintada village in Surkhet
district. One policeman were injured in the clash that lasted five
hours.
</P>
<P>
In another cross-fire between the police and the guerrillas
that took place late Monday in Pyuthan district, five policemen
were killed the reports said.
</P>
<P>
About 1,300 people, including guerrillas, police and civilians,
have been killed during the four-year guerrilla war that started
in 1996. 
</P>
