<HEADLINE> Key Conspirator in Hijack Case Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- India's Central Bureau of
Investigation (CBI) has arrested a key conspirator in the
hijacking of the Indian Airlines flight IC-814 at the end of last
year on charges of procuring and supplying weapons to the
hijackers, the Hindu newspaper reported here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The arrested person, identified as Kumar Bhujel, was picked up
by the CBI on Monday in the state of West Bengal in northeast
India, said the Hindu.
</P>
<P>
It quoted sources as saying that Kumar Bhujel had played a "key
role" in procuring pistols, revolvers and bullets which were later
passed onto the hijackers of the IC-814 flight.
</P>
<P>
The Indian Airlines aircraft was taken by the hijackers on
December 24 after its departure from Kathmandu, Nepal, and was
held in Kandahar, Afghanistan until December 31 when the Indian
government released three jailed militants according to the demand
of the hijackers.
</P>
<P>
Hunting for suspects involved in the hijack case started across
India before the hijack drama came to an end and a dozen people
have since been arrested. 
</P>
</TEXT>
