<HEADLINE> Brazil Registers 26 Million Dollar Surplus in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Brazil registered in the first
quarter of this year a trade surplus of 26 million U.S. dollars,
said the Ministry of Development, Industry and Foreign Trade on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A positive balance came about with exports reaching 12.048
billion dollars and imports totaling 12.022 billion dollars in the
first three months of 2000, said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
In January, Brazil's foreign trade registered a deficit of 94
million dollars, but reversed the trend by gaining 78 million
dollars and 42 million dollars in surplus respectively and in
February and March.
</P>
<P>
In March, manufactured exports grew 26.6 percent over the same
month of the previous year. 
