<HEADLINE> Chinese, Swedish Companies Cooperate In Developing Mobile Internet Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Ericsson (China) Co., Ltd and
China Motion Network Co., Ltd signed an agreement recently to
jointly develop the mobile Internet market in China, Xinhua has
learned.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, Ericsson will provide advisory
services and mobile application platforms, such as Wireless
Application Protocol (WAP), mobile e-mail box platform and
Bluetooth technology, and also offer Business-to-Business
settlement scheme for mobile Internet retail sales.
</P>
<P>
China Motion Network Co., Ltd is mainly engaged in selling
telecommunications products on the Internet and providing
information on mobile phones and related services. It also offers
service platforms for telecommunications products manufacturers
and sellers and develops WAP technologies.
</P>
<P>
The company recently developed an Internet access card which
makes it a reality to roam across the country. So far, 103 cities
have been connected with the network. 
