<DOCNO> XIE20000405.0287 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Exempts Transit Fee on ASEAN Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has exempted collection of
transit fee on goods for fellow member countries of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), according to the
latest issue of the local Business journal.
</P>
<P>
The exemption was to take effect from February 1 this year on
goods carried through prescribed route in accordance with the
ASEAN Framework Agreement on the Facilitation of Goods in Transit,
the Business journal quoted a recent announcement of the Myanmar
Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN framework agreement was endorsed at the association's
4th Meeting of Transport Ministers held in Singapore in September
1998.
</P>
<P>
Later in September 1999, the ASEAN transport ministers agreed
again at their 5th meeting in Hanoi to set the timetable to have
the agreement operationalized by December 31 this year.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Brunei, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia,
Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
