<HEADLINE> Ukraine Rebukes Russia on Bilateral Delimitation Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV April 4, (Xinhua) -- An official with the Ukrainian
Foreign Ministry today rebuked Russia for ending the bilateral
land-delimitation negotiations without providing a good reason.
</P>
<P>
Yuri Kostenko, the Ukrainian envoy for delimitation
negotiations, expressed his uneasiness with Russia for excusing
itself from attending the 13th bilateral negotiation session
scheduled last January.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine had offered to host the session in its northeast Sumy
City several times, but the offer was declined by Russia for "
technical reasons" time and again.
</P>
<P>
Kostenko said the ministry presented a memo to the Russian
Ambassador to Kiev in February on Russia's unilateral decision to
cease negotiations, but there has been no answer from the Russian
side so far.
</P>
<P>
The two country's agreed to finish their land-delimitation
negotiations this summer when Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov
visited Ukraine last October.
</P>
<P>
The envoy denied that both sides had encountered irreconcilable
problems that could disrupt the negotiations, while admitting some
differences between the two parties did exist.
</P>
<P>
He said he expected that acceptable solutions for every problem
could be found by the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
