<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Urges Albania's Cooperation in Curbing Illegal Emigration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Italy has requested the Albanian
government to step up its efforts to prevent illegal emigration.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Albanian Public Security Minister Spartak
Poci, visiting Italian Deputy Interior Minister Mari Tati said
Albania must take vigorous measures to prevent illegal emigration
from Albania to Italy, and that both countries should make efforts
to pursue Albanian criminals hiding in Italy.
</P>
<P>
Poci promised Tati that Albanian police authorities will make
all efforts to thwart illegal emigration to Italy from Albania's
territory.
</P>
<P>
When meeting Albanian Deputy Prime Minister Makb Ule Ceco
earlier in the day, Tati said Italy has decided to increase the
quota of legal Albanian immigrants to 6,000 per year.
</P>
<P>
For her part, Ceco urged the Italian government to accept more
Albanian immigrants and liberalize the granting of visas for
Albanians in order to prevent illegal immigration.
</P>
<P>
Italy, separated from Albania by a narrow strait, has been a
major destination for illegals from Albania in recent years. Since
1992, the number of Albanians entering Italy illegally has grown
every year. For this, the Italian government has frequently urged
Albania to curb the illegal emigration to Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
