<HEADLINE> Yoshiro Mori Elected New LDP President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Yoshiro Mori, secretary general of
Japan's ruling Liberal Democratic Party (LDP), was elected new
president of the party Wednesday to succeed ailing Prime Minister
Keizo Obuchi.
</P>
<P>
Mori, a close ally of Obuchi, was elected at a joint plenary
meeting attended by LDP members of both houses of the Diet (
parliament).
</P>
<P>
Mori, 62, leader of a major LDP faction, is expected to be
picked as Japan's 55th prime minister in the Diet later in the day
as he has already secured support of all LDP factions as well as
LDP's two coalition partners, the New Komeito party and the newly
launched Conservative Party.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi was hospitalized early Sunday after suffering a stroke,
He was later moved to the intensive care unit of a Tokyo hospital
and was put on a respirator. 
