<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Build More Expressways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- China's leading industrial and
commercial city of Shanghai plans to build 13 expressways with a
total length of 650 km over the next decade.
</P>
<P>
The expressways, which are expected to connect Shanghai with
major surrounding cities, will cost 41 billion yuan (4.9 billion U.
S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
An official with the municipal government said that seven
billion yuan of the capital needed will be provided by the
government, with the rest being raised from other sources,
including overseas investors and bank loans.
</P>
<P>
A series of preferential policies will be formulated to attract
both domestic and foreign investors, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai aims to become an international center of finance,
trade, information, and shipping, and has accelerated the
construction of infrastructure in the past years.
</P>
<P>
The city has already constructed expressways to Hangzhou,
capital of nearby Zhejiang Province, and Nanjing, capital of
Jiangsu Province. The city now has expressways with a total
length of 91 kilometers. 
</P>
