<HEADLINE> China-made Bamboo Clothes Popular in Europe, US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Garments made of bamboo by a
Chinese company have become popular in Europe and the United
States.
</P>
<P>
The Nanfang Bamboo and Wood Products Co. Ltd., based in Jinyun
County in east China's Zhejiang Province can produce about 400 man-
made such suits every month and exports all abroad.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1984, the company originally made bamboo
steamers, chopsticks and mats. It started making bamboo clothing
in 1997, by cutting bamboo into thin threads and making them soft
and flexible through special treatment. After that, the bamboo
threads are woven into garments of different designs.
</P>
<P>
The clothes were first put on show at the Guangzhou Trade Fair
in October of 1998, and were warmly welcomed by business people
from the Netherlands, France, Japan and north America.
</P>
<P>
The company invested 500,000 yuan (about 60,240 US dollars) in
developing machinery to expand output.  
</P>
</TEXT>
