<HEADLINE> Academy of Sciences to Build Science Library </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences (
CAS) is planning to build an open digital national science library
based on its own book and information system to provide better
service for the whole country.
</P>
<P>
The information system of the CAS is composed of five science
literature and information centers and libraries of more than 120
research institutes.
</P>
<P>
In order to build the computerized science library, the CAS
will use advanced Internet technology to renovate the whole system
and connect all the information providers with computer network.
</P>
<P>
The national science library will be able to provide round-the-
clock information service for users all across the country, and
the CAS will co-operate with the China Science and Technology Net
(CSTnet) to build a more powerful and comprehensive information
platform.
</P>
<P>
The library is aimed to meet the need of economic development
and will help promote the implementation of the country's major
strategies on scientific and educational progress, said Guo
Chuanjie, vice-president of the CAS.  
</P>
</TEXT>
