<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Simplifies Process for Cross-border Traders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Russian business people may cross
the border into China at Manzhouli, in north China's Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region, and do business for one day without
needing visas.
</P>
<P>
The new regulations save the visitors about 40 percent of the
time they normally used to complete border-crossing procedures,
and have helped double the number of Russian traders who make
deals in China to a daily average of 570 persons.
</P>
<P>
Yang Hanzhong, mayor of Manzhouli, said that the decision was
made for the convenience of Russian merchants. By doing so,
Manzhouli hopes to benefit from its cross-border trade zone, set
up with an investment of over 300 million yuan (about 36 million
US dollars), and attract two billion yuan (about 241 million US
dollars) in foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese decision has urged the Russian side to make the
same approach. It is said that a cross-border trade zone on the
Russian side will be completed within one year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
