<HEADLINE> Border Passenger Transport Operational in Guangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region has opened a border passenger transport route
linking its Pingxiang port with Lang Son in Viet Nam.
</P>
<P>
The international transport route is about 40 km long,
according to a local transportation official. Buses shuttle
between the two ports four times per day.
</P>
<P>
The transport project is jointly run by Zhongning Transport Ltd.
of Guangxi and a Lang Son-based transport company, the official
said, adding that the opening of the transport route will help
boost Sino-Vietnamese border trade and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi is also planning to open a water-land passenger
transport route from its capital city of Nanning to Vinh Ha Long
in Viet Nam. 
</P>
