<HEADLINE> Chinese National English Competition In Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The "21st Century Cup" top prize
in the Fifth National English Speaking Competition held in this
capital of south China's Guangdong Province, went to Chen Heng, a
student at Shanghai Foreign Languages University.
</P>
<P>
Chen will fly to London in May to participate in an
international English speaking competition.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-four students from major universities across the country
took part in the competition, which was judged by a panel of ten
Chinese and foreign English teachers or professors.
</P>
<P>
The contestants were asked to speak on "My View on Success", to
be followed by an impromptu speech, and then a question-and-answer
session.
</P>
<P>
The competition is the highest-level English language contest
in China, and is recognized internationally.
</P>
<P>
The first "21st Century Cup" competition was sponsored by the "
China Daily" newspaper in 1996.
</P>
