<HEADLINE> 24 New Zealand Soldiers in E. Timor Get Fevers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-four new Zealand
soldiers serving in East Timor have caught malaria or dengue fever,
the Dominion reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Wellington-based newspaper quoted Captain Karen Webster of
the New Zealand Defense Force as saying that 14 cases of malaria
and 10 cases of dengue fever have been identified among the New
Zealand contingent.
</P>
<P>
Though all 10 cases of dengue fever were contracted and
diagnosed in East Timor, five of the 14 malaria cases were
identified only after the soldiers returned home, he added.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that there are now more than 600 New Zealand
officers and men serving in East Timor. 
</P>
