<HEADLINE> Tourism Regulations for Northeast China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Jilin Province Tourism
Management Measures, the province's first regulations governing
tourism, recently went into effect.
</P>
<P>
The regional rules are expected to promote provincial tourism
based on the appropriate development of tourism resources and the
protection of the rights and interests of tourists, a local
official said.
</P>
<P>
The regulations state that administration authorities will make
feasibility studies concerning environmental protection before
any new construction of tourism facilities or the development of
scenic spots.
</P>
<P>
Located in northeast China and at the foot of famous
Changbaishan Mountain, Jilin Province is known for its virgin
forests, snowy mountains, and distinctive minority peoples, which
attract tens of thousands of Chinese and overseas travelers every
year. 
