<HEADLINE> More Volunteer Service Expected This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- More than 15 million volunteers
will be involved in various activities under a new program this
year.
</P>
<P>
"It's a dramatic campaign designed to be part of the
International Year of Volunteers, which is next year," Lu
Yongzheng, vice-director of China Volunteer Service Center, was
quoted as saying by today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen government departments, such as the Ministry of
Education, are major sponsors of the volunteer program.
</P>
<P>
The program focuses on community service, poverty elimination
and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Volunteers will continue their work of planting trees to help
preserve the soil along major rivers, in community service to help
build a comprehensive social workers' service and in providing
technology and free education to the hinterlands.
</P>
<P>
Part of the volunteers are expected to conduct on-the-spot
inspections in state-owned enterprises to help them become better
managed and more efficient. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
