<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Office Waste Causes Concern in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- A special office under the State
Environmental Protection Administration has begun a series of
activities to collect and recycle office waste related to the
information industry, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The Office of China Green Channel and the Beijing Industrial
Hazardous Waste Management Center will place special collection
bins for those willing to pay for collecting and sorting the waste.
</P>
<P>
Used batteries, computers, printers, printing accessories and
other office equipment are items that the IT companies often
discard for recycling.
</P>
<P>
According to the office founded on the eve of last year's World
Environment Day, clients would put waste into the bins after
sorting it. The office and its partners would gather it.
</P>
<P>
Then, environmental protection authorities would dismantle and
dispose of the waste, said Yang Jingzeng, director of the office.
</P>
<P>
So far, the office has built seven disposal centers across the
nation, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
