<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit said that the
ruling coalition leaders will continue to push for the extension of
President Suleyman Demirel's term in office, despite objections
from the opposition and some coalition deputies.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit made the remarks in a written statement on Monday after
meeting his coalition partners, Nationalist Movement Party (MHP)
leader and Deputy Prime Minister Devlet Bahceli, and Motherland
Party (ANAP) Chairman Mesut Yilmaz, Turkish Daily News reported
Tuesday. (Turkey-President's Term)
</P>
<P>
MUSCAT -- Arab-Israeli talks on water resources, due to be held
in Muscat on April 11-12, have been cancelled as Oman would not act
as a host due to its obligations to the Arab League.
</P>
<P>
An Omani foreign ministry source said his country has not
invited member countries of the working group on water under the
multilateral negotiations, which include Israel, to hold such
talks. (Arab-Israel-Water Talks)
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Two civilians were killed and a number of people
injured in U.S. and British warplanes' attacks in southern and
northern Iraq on Tuesday, an Iraqi military spokesman announced.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that at 12:50 (0950GMT), 16 formations of U.
S. and British planes made 38 armed sorties from Saudi Arabia and
Kuwait, bombing civilian and service facilities in the southern
provinces of Basra, Misan, Thi-Qar, Qadissiyah, Wasit, Muthana and
Najaf, killing two and injuring an unspecified number of people.
(Iraq-U.S.-Attacks)
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Chairman of the Palestinian National Authority (PNA)
Yasser Arafat said the Palestinian-Israeli final status talks were
still in a preliminary stage.
</P>
<P>
"None of the main topics has been resolved so far," he told
reporters after meeting visiting Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev at his presidential office in the West Bank city of
Ramallah on Tuesday. (Arafat-Final Status-Talks)
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The first-ever Africa-Europe summit ended here on
Tuesday with the issuing of a final declaration and adopting of a
plan of action.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak, Algerian President Abdelaziz
Bouteflika, Secretary General of the Organization of African Unity
Salem Amhad Salem and European Union (EU) Foreign Affairs and
Security Coordinator Javier Solana addressed the closing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Hailing the summit as having succeeded in reflecting the depth
of historical relations between Africa and Europe, Mubarak said it
also was able to come up with joint positive visions of how the two
continents' future should be like. (EU-Africa-Summit) 
</P>
