<HEADLINE> U.N. Security Council to Visit Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Security
Council has reached an agreement to pay a visit to Kosovo by the
end of this month, U.N. announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
U.N. Acting Deputy Spokesman David Wimhurst said the visit
will take place on April 28 and 29.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the mission is aimed to observe the
operations of the U.N. Interim Administration Mission in Kosovo(
UNMIK) and convey a message to all concerned on the need to reject
violence.
</P>
<P>
The mission will be headed by Ambassador Anwarul Karim
Chowdhury of Bangladesh, who chaired the Security Council In March,
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Wimhurst said the composition of the mission is still being
under discussion.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council agreed last week to visit Kosovo
following an appeal by the head of UNMIK, Bernard Kouchner, who
briefed a private meeting of the Council early last month, the
spokesman added. 
</P>
