<HEADLINE> Brazil, Mexico Sign Photographic Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the publication, the good results reached by the
sector are due to the strategy applied by the negotiators in both
countries, consisting in starting talks sticking to the list of
products known as "coincident", which make up the petition lists
in both countries, thus, enabling an agreement.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian and Mexican lists, each, elaborated from the
private sector proposals, contain nearly 1,270 articles, of which
290 are coincident.
</P>
<P>
Both countries' business sector, not participating directly in
the government negotiations, forecasts that there will be new
achievements during the next meeting , programmed for April 17 and
19 at Mexico City.
</P>
<P>
A custom preference agreement will also be signed before
president Zedillo's presidential term is over, that is, before
Mexican presidential elections due next July 2.
</P>
<P>
The official proposal is to negotiate the agreement until next
June, with an initial period of two year, said Lucia Maduro, from
Brazil's Industry National Confederation's International
Integration Unit. 
