<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's Somali State to Get More Relief Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia is preparing to
transport a new batch of 16,600 tons of food aid to
drought-stricken areas in Somali State, the state authority
announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The relief food, enough for one month ration, would be
dispatched shortly to various zones of the state affected by
drought due to rain failure in four consecutive rainy seasons,
said Sultan Ibrahim, secretary of the state's administration.
</P>
<P>
Somali State is one of the states hit by the current drought in
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
So far more than 26,800 tons of relief grain released by the
government have been distributed among drought affected people in
the state over the past four months, Sultan said.
</P>
<P>
The state government is also apportioning safe drinking water
among the drought victims, he said. 
</P>
