<HEADLINE> Nine Forest Fires Break Out in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, April 5 (Xinhua) -- A total of nine forest fires broke
out in different parts of Greece over the past twenty-four hours.
</P>
<P>
The most serious of the forest fires broke out in four
different parts of the eastern Aegean island of Samos, and strong
winds hindered efforts to set it under control, the semi-official
Athens News Agency (ANA) reported Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
In the Kydonia region of Hania prefecture on the southern
Greek island of Crete, two forest fires were reported while a
forest fire also broke out in Achaia prefecture in the
southwestern Peloponnese peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Other forest fires broke out in Drama, northern Greece and on
the island of Evoia.
</P>
<P>
Although a large number of fire engines and fire fighters have
rushed to battle the blazes, strong winds and lack of road
infrastructure reportedly hamper the fire fighting efforts.
</P>
